The paper presents a method that uses machine learning techniques to predict the future states of interacting agents based on partial observations. This involves learning a dynamics model and a vision model, and integrating temporal and visual information using a graph-structured variational recurrent neural network. The paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), as it involves training a neural network to make predictions. It could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as it involves developing a system that can reason about the behavior of multiple agents. Additionally, the paper uses computer vision techniques to process visual information, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The use of a graph-structured model suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics), as this is a common approach in robotics research. Finally, the paper involves predicting the behavior of multiple agents, which could place it under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
